For any brides who want to save money on a wedding but don’t want to compromise a lot of what you want, have a wedding in the off-season (November-March). My wedding is in January and We got half price photographer, discount on the venue and flexibility in times, discount on catering, free engagement photos, discount on video, and a free photo booth. All would have been pricey in the spring/summer! It was all very nice and some of it we wouldn’t have been able to afford in season. Because of all the savings, it is in our budget to afford more food and an open bar. I also recommend looking to see if any high end boutiques have off the rack dresses. I bought a beautiful long sleeved, hand beaded Justin Alexander dress that retails for $3,000...I bought it for $1250 because it was past season and missing some beading. It was in the size it would have been ordered for me and every dress needs alterations anyway. It was more unique and honestly prettier than every $5000-6000 dress I saw in the boutique.
